          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross-section measurements for neutron-induced",
                " reactions in copper at neutron energies of 70.7 and",
                " 110.8 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAHRV"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " k = 200 split sector cyclotron"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-BE"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Quasi-monoenergetic neutron beams of 70.7 MeV",
                " and 110.8 MeV, respectively were produced by directing",
                " 79.4 and 118 MeV pulsed proton beams (4-10 microA)",
                " onto a 10 mm thick Beryllium target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE-IN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High purity Ge detectors plus pulse height",
                "  analyzers with computer data acquisition systems",
                "  located at iTL and the Northeast Proton Therapy",
                " Center (NPTC) were used to measure non-destructively",
                " the yields of the short-lived products produced in the",
                " Cu monitor foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "SiO2 target, (50 x 50 mm) be 9 mm thick; Cu foils"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The yields of relatively short-lived",
                " radionuclides produced in the targets and monitor",
                " foils were measured using non-destructive gamma-ray",
                " spectroscopy."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron time-of-flight spectra measured (for the",
                " same monitor count) at 0 degree and 16 degree,",
                " respectively were compared in order to determine the",
                " factors required for this normalization."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cu monitor foils, 15 mm in diameter and 1 mm thick",
                " (Good fellow Corp. purity 99.99+%) were placed",
                " immediately downstream of the SiO2 target, together",
                " with aluminum, nickel and gold monitor foils and, for",
                " stability, the entire target stackwas wrapped in Al",
                " foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total error in the cross-section",
                " measurement was obtained by adding in quadrature, the",
                " following individual errors: 2% for the number of",
                " target atoms; the estimated error in the measurement",
                " of the neutron fluence, about 7%; 5% for the error in",
                " the Ge detector efficiency; and the statistical",
                " counting error"
              ]
            }
          ],
